cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and discourse parsing. The use of a graph convolutional network also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves classification tasks, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of semantic information and discourse relations could also suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
